6 An Act relating to schools; amending Section 2,
Chapter 281, O.S.L. 2023, as amended by Section 2,
7 Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
5-148.2), which relates to the School Security
8 Revolving Fund; removing expenditure limitation;
requiring certain amount of funds to be allocated
9 from the fund each fiscal year for three fiscal years
beginning on certain date, subject to available
10 funding; providing an effective date; and declaring
an emergency.
11
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY Section 2, Chapter 281, O.S.L.
15 2023, as amended by Section 2, Chapter 408, O.S.L. 2024 (70 O.S.
16 Supp. 2025, Section 5-148.2), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 5-148.2. A. There is hereby created in the State
18 Treasury a revolving fund for the State Department of Education to
19 be designated the “School Security Revolving Fund”. The fund shall
20 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
21 shall consist of all monies received by the State Department of
22 Education from:
23 1. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from other
24 state agencies and entities for school security;
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1189 Page 1

1 2. Reimbursements, grants, or other monies received from the
2 United States government obligated to school security projects;
3 3. Gifts, donations, and bequests; and
4 4. Monies appropriated or apportioned by the Legislature.
5 B. All monies accruing to the credit of the School Security
6 Revolving Fund are hereby appropriated and may be budgeted and
7 expended by the State Department of Education for the purposes of:
8 1. Establishing and maintaining a School Resource Officer
9 Program; and
10 2. Providing physical security enhancements for schools
11 including, but not limited to, school resource officers, cameras,
12 gates, lighting, locks, doors, windows, security geofencing,
13 ballistic storm shelters, and mobile panic alert systems.
14 Monies in the School Security Revolving Fund shall supplement
15 and not supplant existing school security funding.
16 C. Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall
17 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
18 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
19 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
20 Expenditures from the School Security Revolving Fund shall not
21 exceed Subject to the availability of funding, Fifty Million Dollars
22 ($50,000,000.00) in any fiscal year and shall be allocated from the
23 School Security Revolving Fund and divided equally among every
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1189 Page 2

1 publ ic school district in the this state each fiscal year for three
2 (3) fiscal years beginning July 1, 2026.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
6 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
7 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
8 Passed the Senate the 24th day of March, 2026.
